BEGIN_PGML
[$p] is buying tea bags and sugar packets. Each tea bag costs [$A] cents, and each sugar packet costs [$B] cents. [$p->They] can spend a total of [$Cd]. Assume [$p] will spend the full amount. Write a linear equation in standard form that models the number of tea bags and sugar packets [$p->they] can purchase.

[@KeyboardInstructions('Associate the number of tea bags with variable [`x`] and the number of sugar packets with variable [`y\text{.}`]')@]**

[_]{$evaluator}{16}

